loss of consciousness; nausea; vomiting; stopped breathing several times for multiple seconds and they described her to be gurgling when her pulse ox went down to 83%; Difficulty breathing; severe Headcahe; This is a spontaneous report received Support from a contactable nurse from Pfizer sponsored program via medical information team. This case pertains to patient 3 of 3. A 15-year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTEC COVID-19 VACCINE, Solution for injection, Lot Number: ER8727; Expiry Date: 31Jul2021), dose 2 via an unspecified route of administration on 17Jun2021 (at the age of 15-year-old) as a single for COVID-19 immunisation. The patient medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. The patient historical vaccine included bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTEC COVID-19 VACCINE), dose 1 via an unspecified route of administration on an unspecified date as a single for COVID-19 immunisation and had no reaction. On 17Jun2021, after 15 minutes of observation, the patient had a severe headache, difficulty breathing, loss of consciousness and stopped breathing several times for multiple seconds and they described her to be gurgling when her pulse ox went down to 83%. On an unspecified date, the patient also had nausea and vomiting. The patient pulse ox (documented as provided by caller) went down to 83%, she had severe headache, nausea, vomiting and she was unconscious. When she was unconscious was when her pulse ox was 83% and she stopped breathing intermittently for 10 to 12 seconds at a time. Then she started breathing again but was not responsive after she received the epinephrine then her pulse ox steadily rose again but was not responsive. She was like this until EMS took her away. The reporter stated that the most severe case was for this particular patient. She had already been vaccinated and had already gone through the 15 minute observation. All these kids came in a bus together, but this patient was sitting in the vehicle after the observation when the guardian brought her back to the nurses saying that she was complaining of a severe headache and at that point she had difficulty breathing and lost consciousness. The nurses reported that it appeared that she stopped breathing several times for multiple seconds and they described her to be gurgling when her pulse ox went down to 83%. At that time they administered epi (epinephrine) and called EMS. Her pulse ox and her breathing improved after the administration of epi, however she remained unresponsive when she was on the way to the hospital with EMS. The patient was taken to the hospital and she did improve. This was the 2nd dose, she had the 1st dose and did not have a reaction to it. The seriousness of the events severe headache, difficulty breathing, loss of consciousness, stopped breathing several times for multiple seconds and they described her to be gurgling when her pulse ox went down to 83% was reported as medically significant. The reporter stated that it was very serious. This patient reaction was a little more intense than just an anxiety induced reaction. She says with a pulse ox of 83% if they had not intervened then this would of been life threatening. It is medically significant but if they had not intervened then it would have been life threatening especially when you're talking about gurgling and a pulse ox of 83%. The reporter tends to think that with that severe of a reaction, with the pulse ox that low and her being unresponsive, she believes that this was probably a true adverse event. Outcome of the events was reported as unknown.  The reported causality for the events severe headache, had difficulty breathing and lost consciousness, stopped breathing several times for multiple seconds and they described her to be gurgling when her pulse ox went down to 83% was reported as related.  Information on Lot/Batch number was available. Additional information has been requested.; Sender's Comments: Based on known drug safety profile, there is reasonable possibility of causal association between the events respiratory arrest, loss of consciousness, dyspnea and headache and the suspect drug.  The impact of this report on the benefit/risk profile of the Pfizer product is evaluated as part of Pfizer procedures for safety evaluation, including the review and analysis of aggregate data for adverse events. Any safety concern identified as part of this review, as well as any appropriate action in response, will be promptly notified to regulatory authorities, Ethics Committees, and Investigators, as appropriate.

MA accidentally injected a 15 month old patient, with only the Daptacel/Ipol portion of the Pentacel vaccine and the patient did not receive the ActHIB powdered portion with no reported adverse event; Initial information regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case was received from the other health professional via Regulatory authority (Reference number- 00642362) and transmitted to Sanofi on 15-Jun-2021.  This case involves a 15-month-old male patient who only received the Daptacel/Ipol portion and did not received the Act-HIB powdered portion, while patient was receiving a 0.5 mL fourth dose of suspect DIPHTHERIA/TETANUS/5 HYBRID AC PERTUSSIS/IPV(MRC5)/HIB(PRP/T) VACCINE [PENTACEL] [Diluent Vial: Lot number: U6986AA, expiry date: 22-Jul-2022, National Drug Code (NDC): 4928156005, Powder: Lot number: UJ529AA, expiry date: 22-Jul-2022, NDC: 4928154858, Box: Lot number: UJ529AAA, expiry date: 22-Jul-2022, NDC: 4928151005, Vaccine presentation: vial] on 15-Jun-2021 for prophylactic vaccination (product preparation issue).   Medical history, medical treatment, vaccination and family history were not reported.  Concomitant medications included PNEUMOCOCCAL VACCINE CONJ 7V (CRM197) (PREVNAR).  It was a case of actual medication error due to inappropriate reconstitution technique. (Latency: same day)  It was reported that, the medical assistant (MA) accidentally injected the only the Daptacel/Ipol portion of the suspect and patient did not received the Act-HIB powder portion.   At the time of report, the MA wanted to know how she can give the ActHIB portion to patient and stated that, the error was occurred because she did not pay attention when she was getting the Pentacel out of the box and did not mix them together. The MA noticed the error after the patient was gone and when she was documenting. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initially I had arm pain, as expected later in the evening on day of shot.  I iced and took Tylenol as advised by staff at health department.  Saturday morning I woke to nausea, lightheadedness and increased arm pain.  I pushed fluid intake, rested off and on all day, took Tylenol as needed.  Sunday morning felt tired, but other symptoms were better so went about the day.  Sunday afternoon I noticed my joints started hurting, and chills set in.  By Monday morning every joint in my body hurt, and not just an ache - because all of my muscles were aching as well - but my toes, ankles, knees, elbows, hips felt like they had been hammered and were throbbing.  I've been taking Tylenol, resting, fluids as tolerated and three days from onset it's still hanging on.  I've never experienced joint pain like this in my life ...

Lung transplant recipient from 9/2018, stable lung function and no significant rejection episodes.  Underwent first dose of COVID19 (Moderna) vaccination 3/22/21 and second dose 4/19/2021.  Developed progressive shortness of breath and presented to transplant clinic 4/26/21 with 30% decline in pulmonary function tests.  Transbronchial biopsies and extensive evaluation for infectious and known immunologic causes of rejection were negative.  Patient had progressive decline in lung function despite high dose augmented immunosuppression and was diagnosed with rapid onset chronic lung allograft dysfunction (bronchiolitis obliterans phenoytpe).  Lung function continued to worsen and she was transitioned to hospice 6/2021.  Spike protein antibody testing showed significant IgG and IgA response.  VAERS reporting being filed given chronologic and potential physiologic association between vaccination and onset of BOS.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the morning of Sunday, June 6, 2021, I woke up with dull pain in the center of my chest (right where the sternum is). My mother took me to urgent care. A doctor there did an EKG with came back slightly abnormal, and she recommended I go to the emergency room. The doctors there ran a few tests. By about noon or so, my chest pain had subsided and has since not returned. My only abnormal test was troponin. After the first troponin test, I was transferred from the ER to an observation area. After the fourth troponin test, Dr. ordered an angiogram. The angiogram occurred on June 8, 2021, at around 5:00 pm or 6:00 pm. It revealed no signs of damage or inflammation. I was discharged from the hospital the morning of June 9, 2021. Since then, I had a follow-up with my primary care provider, on June 15, 2021, and with the Dr. on June 23, 2021. Neither of them detected anything wrong with my heart. To summarize, I went to the hospital with chest pain that subsided quickly and has not returned since, and I remained in the hospital with elevated troponin.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The following day I was shaking uncontrollable head to toe.  I could feel nothing but pain.  If 10 was the standard before, this was 20-25.  a month later a storm came and I had the exact same pain issues and the same pain levels.  I went to see my rheumatologist and told him my issues.  He sent me to a neurologist and scheduled an appointment with a pain clinic.  The rheumatologist gave me a prescription for gabapentin after than, 300 mg two times a day, and it has seemed to help, but my pain problems are getting worse.  It is now 3 months later and I am quickly loosing the ability to hand the pain.  I have been in none stop pain for the last 18 hours.  I am taking a 7.5mg/325 mg pill of Tylenol three that I got from the pain clinic, but it is barely holding the pain back.  I have never felt pain like this in all my days.

This was supposed to be a follow up for the MRI, but the orders got lost.  Resent order.   Pain Clinic - 0900 on May 21st, 21.  This was my initial appointment with the pain clinic to go over my options.  They then suggested I get injections in my knees and lower spin to deal with pain issues related to Psoriatic Arthritis. (Update: Still waiting on MRI's to get to pain clinic before insurance will cover injections.)  Medical Center  - April 8th, 21.  I set this appointment up after talking with my dermatologist and managed to see my rheumatologist that same day.  I told him of all the pain issues and he had me do some tests.  He noticed weakness when I tried to stand up and a great deal of shaking.  Scheduled me for bloodwork, to see a neurologist, and for the pain clinic.   Dermatology Clinic - April 8th, 21. I had told my dermatologist that I was still having pain issues of an extreme nature a month after my vaccination.  They suggested strongly that I talk to my rheumatologist.  I setup the appointment to see him that day.

Spent the day in bed. Each time I would get up, I would feel as if I were going to faint. The next day felt better BUT when I was walking outside, I would get extremely dizzy, would have difficulties breathing, heart palpitations and my legs would become very heavy. At rest most of the symptoms would go away.  On June 18 I saw a doctor addressing my symptoms. The doctor suspected acid reflux but still wanted to do CT scan of lungs because I had stopped birth control pills a month or so before the vaccination. Also I was prescribed Pantoprazole. During the next two weeks I was getting much worse. The heart rate was racing ? 100-120 at rest, I was dizzy, not able to walk my dog or walk around the house at some days. Each time I walked I felt as if I was going to faint.  On June 1 I felt very dizzy walking around the house. Basically I could not take 5 steps without feeling dizzy. So I called an urgent care doctor. I was sent to have a blood test (to look for thrombosis signs) and EKG. The blood test came back normal. EKG was ?borderline? ? ?Borderline Right Axis Deviation Cors Axis >90?.  On June 9 I got CT scan which came back normal. Still, I was very weak and dizzy.  On June 14 I was given a Holter monitor for 3 days (ending June 17). As if today, June 23 I don?t have the results from the monitor.  Today I feel better, however, I still have joint pain and my legs get extremely heavy and painful after performing daily routine activities.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient felt like he was having an asthma attack on the night of the 21st when playing outside with friends (running and climbing). He has never had asthma, but said his chest was tight and it was hard to breathe. He said when he stopped and sat for a while it seemed to get better. He went to sleep at about 2am and woke me up at 5:20am crying. His chest hurt really bad and the pain was traveling down his arm. When we took his blood pressure at home it was 205/125 and his heart rate was 112. We went to the emergency room at hospital immediately. Once there they did an EKG. The doctor said there was not reason to be alarmed, but the EKG showed signs of possible pericarditis. They then took blood work, a urine sample, an xray and did an echocardiogram. The doctor told us that the blood work did not show any signs of an actual heart attack or any damage done to the heart. She said the echocardiogram showed some fluid build up in the pericardia sac surrounding his heart. She said this is considered pericardia. She mentioned that some young men are having this happen after being vaccinated. She said we seem to have caught it early. They gave him Tordal through his IV when we were there and that took his pain away. We were told to follow up with a cardiologist within 24-48 hours. We have an appointment at Hospital tomorrow at 10:45am.
LAB_DATA: 6/22 EKG - abnormal urine - normal blood - normal echocardiogram - showed fluid build up in pericardia sac

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After first shot an uptick in paranoia as every day got worse.  Before second shot I was having the vivid dreams.  I was also hearing, seeing, smelling, tasting things that weren't there.  The second shot put me over the edge immediately.  I felt as if I was being poisoned, the vial with medicine inside turned amber color and I shut down as paranoia turned into an orchestrated conspiracy against me.  for the next 3- 4 weeks I hallucinated daily,  I believed reality was a dream and fiction was my reality.  My wife tried multiple times to make me understand that what I was going through was not real, yet because my paranoia and psychosis I remained shut down and basically sleeping for two weeks. I could not speak about what was going on b/c I could not formulate a tangible and coherent thought.  During this time I believed everyone was against me, which now I know is not true.  It was a nightmare that lasted months.  On June 4th I saw Dr., whom recommended a psychologist.  I was able to book the first appointment on June 15th and have been going to Dr. on a weekly basis.  The internal hysteria, paranoia, hallucinations kept me mute for about a month.  About a month after my second shot I began to speak about it although it was disjointed.  It was on May 13th.  It took weeks of trying to formulate thoughts to go to a doctor.  I am still having issues remembering words.  Psychologist suggests I see a neurologist.  That is why it has taken me so long to report.

6/19/21 patient awoke with non-bloody, bright green emesis and abdominal pain. She endorses several episodes of nonbloody diarrhea with continued abdominal pain.  She endorses starting her menstrual period 3 days ago. Mom endorses fever at this time, T-max 102.9.  Presented to an urgent care for further evaluation where they obtained a rapid strep test and COVID-19 swab that were both negative. 6/21/21 she presented to an ED for continued and worsening symptoms.  She received a dose of antibiotics and saline boluses during transfer to another hospital.  In route, she became hypotensive with minimal response to fluid resuscitation. She required vasopressors to maintain blood pressure. A CT of the abdomen showed nonspecific findings for enterocolitis.  A urinalysis had 5-15 RBCs and 51-100 WBCs. She was started on antibiotics. She required ICU admission initially, but improved and became hemodynamically stable after about 16 hours in the PICU. Her urine culture grew 3 different organisms with low colony counts so antibiotics were discontinued on 6/22/21. A repeat ECHO the following day revealed normal biventricular size and systolic function, mild tricuspid regurgitation estimating RV systolic pressure of 30mmHg, left main coronary artery appears slightly prominent but measures within normal limits. LMCA measurement is similar to previous, normal measurement of the proximal RCA and LAD, and trivial pericardial effusion. The patient also had an elevated CRP of 18.8 mg/dL, fibrinogen of 408 mg/dL, d-dimer of 0.98, and nt-pro BNP of 309. SARS CoV2 IgG was positive and IgM was negative. She received IVIG 100 gm on 6/23/21 and was started on rivaroxaban. CRP decreased to 8.2 mg/dL on 6/23/21.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my first dose of the COVID 19 vaccine on the 2nd of May. Approximately a week or two later I started developing 2 unique symptoms not experienced before. First, I started getting a burning sensation across my left chest that would come and go. Second,  I started to develop pain every time I bent my thumb or pressed in the area of the metacarpal joint on my right hand. This persisted, and the week of May the 26th the burning sensation in my chest was getting stronger and the event lasting longer. It has now been a few weeks, and the symptoms were getting worse. It was enough concern to call my sister who is a nurse whom recommended I go to an urgent care. On the 26th of May I went to an urgent care. They stated that I should go to the hospital as they do not have the equipment to properly diagnose. I went to Hospital ER at approximately 4PM. It was there that I did blood work, got an EKG upon arriving and upon leaving, and x-rays of the heart. The outcome was that the physical exam, blood work, x-rays, and EKG did not show anything of major concern. The ER doctor thinks it is somehow related to the heart muscle surrounding the heart. I received baby aspirin, menthol patch, and was told to take ibuprofen as needed. For my thumb issue, I visited my chiropractor on 16 June 2021 and asked about the joint issues in the thumb, and he recommended to see my family doctor. He thinks it might be arthritis related. I am working to schedule an appointment.

Patient reports that 3 days ago, he received the 2nd COVID-19 vaccination (Pfizer ) in his left anterior deltoid area.  Following this he developed diffuse body aches and headaches.   On day prior to admission, patient developed fever at home with T-max 101.8� F. after going to sleep, he was awoken with nausea.  Patient experienced episodes of vomiting, which he reported mostly consist of water, and also reported left arm and left chest pain at this time.  He reports the pain felt like pressure and was a severity of 9/10.  Patient also experienced numbness and tingling in his left hand.  He attempted to take Tums and Motrin at home with mild relief of symptoms.  Mother then brought patient in to Emergency Room.  Patient denies syncope, no palpitations, pain does not worsen with deep breathing, pain unchanged by position.. emergency department course:  Presented with temperature 99.7� F, heart rate 92, blood pressure 138/90, saturating 98% on room air.   Laboratory work revealed elevated troponin, elevated CK-MB, and elevated creatine kinase.  Chest x-ray was performed which was normal.  EKG revealed normal sinus rhythm.  Patient was transferred to our emergency room and subsequently admitted to the floor.       Hospital Course: He was evaluated in Hospital Emergency Room and admitted to the floor for more close monitoring.  His repeat labs showed elevated troponin and an echocardiogram was unremarkable.  In view of the elevated troponin was case was discussed with the cardiologist who recommended a cardiac MRI which was performed which did reveal myocarditis, pericarditis.  In view of this ICU service is consulted for admission closer monitoring further evaluation management.

Prescribed a Heart Monitor for 14 days and released at approximately 5:00 PM.   Third occurrence was Monday May 31.  Heart attack symptoms chest pain, accelerated heart rate.   Went into AFIB.   Transported to Hospital.  (Morton Plant).  Verified AFIB reading by heart monitor.  Admitted to the hospital for two days.  EKG monitors, Blood tests.   Released Tuesday at 4:00 PM.  Prescribed Multaq by on call Cardiologist to prevent AFIB.    Met with Cardiologist Monday June 7th.  Diagnosed as Pericarditis or myocarditis. The patient is a 53 yo previously healthy male who experienced GBS temporally associated with receipt of Pfizer BioNTech COVID vaccine (lot # EW0162 )13 APR 2021. He denies any illness symptoms such as fever, malaise, cough, URI symptoms, n/v/d in the preceding month. He denies any immediate reaction suggestive of IgE mediated event. He reports his initial only side effect was local site tenderness. Approximately 11 days after receipt he had been playing basketball with his kids during the. day and he noted unusual fatigue that evening, pain in his shoulders/neck, took ibuprofen and went to be early. In the morning (Day 14), his right leg slipped and he fell when standing after getting out of bed. He took a few steps and discovered he had no balance and fell again. Family brought him to ER. He was evaluated but no definitive diagnosis and discharged home. He reports on 29 APR 21 (day 16) he was brushing his teeth and couldn't retain water in his mouth. He noted facial drooping, his speech was affected and he returned to ER. ER eval was inconclusive but he was admitted for further evaluation. after multiple tests including LP he was diagnosed with atypical GBS. He received IVIG and was transferred to hospital. This patient was in clinic for a primary care visit, with her mother, and decided to receive her 1st dose of Pfizer. The clinic assistant that administered the vaccine  accidentally prepared the vaccine with 0.18 mL of diluent (as opposed to the required 1.8 mL) and then proceeded to administer 0.3 mL of this concentrated preparation. This resulted in  the patient receiving a higher-than-authorized dose of Pfizer-- just under 6 doses. This error was caught within a few minutes after administration because a different staff member was drawing up a dose of Pfizer from that vial and realized there was not enough left in the vial, even though only 1 dose was recorded on the vial. This staff member immediately realized there was likely an error in the preparation and informed me. I had the staff member that prepared the vaccine walk me through the process they used and we realized her error of only adding 0.18 mL of diluent.  Per CDC  COVID-19 Vaccine Administration Errors and Deviation guidelines, the patient and her mother were immediately notified  of the error and the potential for adverse side effects, a report was made internally, and another health authority was contacted to verify the correct way to enter the error in the system. The patient was  kept in office for observation for 30 minutes post vaccination. The mother of the patient and the patient asked to leave once the 30 minutes was up as the patient denied symptoms. One of our RNs is going to contact the patient tomorrow morning. The patient and mother were advised to call the clinic with any concerns and new symptoms. They were also given ED precautions.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within ten (10) minutes of receiving second Covid-19 Pfizer vaccine, my left arm and hand went numb and tingly.  An attending nurse completed various tests ruling out emergency treatment at that time, indicating I should see advice from my Primary Care Physician if side affects persisted the next day.  The following day, the numbing/tingling expanded from the top of my head, all the way down the left side of my face, neck, arm, hand, lower leg and foot.  I was seen by my Primary Care Physician who directed me  immediately to the Emergency Room of Medical Center, as he thought I could be having a stroke or have a blood clot due to the affects of the Covid-19 Pfizer vaccine. With my symptoms continuing and worsening and blood pressure extremely high, I had blood drawn, was given an EKG and a CT Scan in the ER.  A neurologist was also consulted who indicated my symptoms heard of after the vaccine but never seen in person.  I was referred by the attending ER Physician, Dr., to follow up with the neurologist, Dr., and was given an appointment for Friday, April 23. 2021.  I was evaluated, then scheduled and received a brain MRI with and without contrast on Wednesday, April 28, 2021.  Tests given at the time in the ER and with the neurologist appeared to show no signs of a stroke, lesions, masses or a heart attack.  The numbing/tingling continued with my left arm, leg and foot continuously for two weeks and moved around to other parts of my body for shorter periods of time during the duration.  After the two weeks, the numbing/tingling sensation appears and disappears quickly (within 30 seconds) in my left arm/hand and left foot.  This does not occur every day but still happens very sporadically.  Note:  The numbing/tingling sensation I felt within my head/face/neck area was consistent with the feeling of receiving novocaine. Please Note:  Approximately 30 minutes after my first Covid-19 Pfizer vaccine, I experienced a numb/tingling in my tongue with slight discomfort and the sensation I had eaten something very acidic.   I experience the same sensation at times after eating tomatoes or oranges.   I could feel my uvula when swallowing and drank a tremendous amount of water.  My throat did not close, nor did I have difficulty breathing.  I took a Benadryl tablet before bedtime, and the sensation was gone the next morning.  I mentioned this affect before receiving my second dose of the Covid-19 Pfizer vaccine.  The nurse checked with others, and it was decided I would be kept for 30 minutes for observation instead of the usual 15 minutes following the vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Flonase, Vitamins, B-12, C and D

There was also a brownish discharge leaking out. Monday morning I made an appointment with my gynecologist, and a nurse practitioner did an exam showed me the genital ulcers and told me it was most likely herpes. They swabbed one of the ulcers and gave me a prescription for Valacyclovir for 10 days. I also took a blood test for HSV1/HSV2 IGG and IGM the next day. For the first 5 days the pain was horrible, worst pain I've ever felt, couldn't walk, stand, sit or sleep. I got my period Wednesday morning which made it even worse.  On Friday morning 5/7/21 I got a call from the nurse practitioner and she said the swab and blood test came back negative, I went back the same day so the doctor could look. They still thought it was herpes and told me to take another blood test in a month. I did not have a prior diagnosis of herpes and showed no symptoms before. My partner of the past 1.5 years got tested for herpes and was also negative. After a month I went took another blood test and it came back negative again for HSV-1 and HSV-2.  The only thing different in my medical history is that I got the vaccine and 36-48 hours later I had herpes symptoms.  These symptoms lasted for 2.5 weeks until I started to no longer feel any pain.

Three days after my first dose of the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine, I had a routine wellness check at my primary care doctor.  They found in my bloodwork that I was very hyperthyroid with nearly undetectable TSH levels and very high T3 and T4.  I was not symptomatic at the time of the initial bloodwork, the only thing I had noticed from the day of my vaccine through the following week was that my resting heart rate had skyrocketed from an average of high 50s to 60bpm to 80+.  By March 18th, I had started to feel intense heart palpitations, sweating, shakiness, and dizziness. Further testing found that I had subacute thyroiditis likely caused by the COVID vaccine.  I ended up going very hypothyroid with high TSH levels a month after the initial testing and am currently on levothyroxine hoping for a full recovery of my thryoid function.  The reason for concluding the vaccine was likely the cause was that I have no history of thyroid issues, had not been recently ill with anything, and it had been 1.5 years since I last had my baby.  I had last had my thyroid tested October 2020 with my OBGYN as part of her routine checks and had normal TSH levels then.  The timing and events led us to conclude the vaccine was likely the cause of the thyroiditis.  I ended up delaying my second dose for six weeks due to the unknown status of my thyroid at the time.  I received my second dose on April 22 and had zero side effects from that second dose.
LAB_DATA: I had bloodwork done on March 16 measuring my TSH and free T4.  TSH was nearly undetectable and T4 was very high.  On March 23, they re-did my bloodwork and found even lower TSH, and very high free T4 and free T3.  I was then referred to an endocrinologist, Dr. with Endocrinology. She found I had an enlarged thyroid gland, and it was painful to touch. She did more bloodwork on March 25 and found antibodies for Graves disease were negative so she referred me for a thyroid uptake/scan.  I had the thyroid uptake/scan done on April 6 and it was found that my uptake was very low. This led Nurse to diagnose me with subacute thyroiditis. On May 10, I had my next appointment with her and did more bloodwork where she found I now had very high TSH and low T3 and T4 making me hypothyroid.  She started me on 50mg of levothyroxine which I've been taking since May 12. I don't meet with Dr. again until the end of June to see how my thyroid is responding to the meds but I do feel much better already.

Around 4/19/21 pt started experiencing shortness of breath that increased to the point of gasping for breath on 4/25/21.  Her daughter (me!) visited and immediately called her pulmonologist who requested she immediately go to the hospital.  The ER said she had an enlarged heart, and was checked in to the cardiac unit.  Tests showed she had acute systolic and diastolic heart failure.  She was first put on diuretics while further tests were done, and Tikosyn was later added to her list of regular medications.  Within a week she was able to go home.  She was on oxygen prior to this event from the pulmonary fibrosis, and was able to return to her prior settings on her oxygen concentrator within five days, but her ongoing discomfort has stayed at a heightened level, and her level of activity has not returned to her normal.  Please note:  she is an 84 year old with pulmonary fibrosis.  It is not possible for me as her daughter (not a medical professional) to know if the original diagnosis of heart inflammation was related to her vaccination, but she had been relatively stable for more than six months prior to this hospitalization event and the onset of this sequence of events was identified by the doctors as being of unknown origin at that time.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: My Pfizer shots were delivered on Feb 18 and March 12, 2021. I experienced irregular menstrual symptoms from March 1-March 13 of 2021. My typical menstrual cycle is 26-28 days, with 3-4 days of concentrated bleeding. My previous 3 periods were Dec 18-22. Jan 17-20, and Feb 12-16. On March 1 almost 2 weeks before my expected period, I started spotting and cramping. The light bleeding continued for 2 weeks, at which time it transitioned into my typical period with regular cramps and bleeding, in line with my usual experience. My GYN did not know what could be causing this (I later found out there have been many irregular menstrual symptoms associated with Covid-19 vaccines. I don't regret getting it, this was fairly mild, but if there is a causitive link between the vaccines and mesntrual side effects, women NEED to know this. Menstrual and female reproductive health side effects need to be observed and measured in clinical trials, and female patients need to be advised what to expect.

I was diagnosed with Lupus at 10 years old and experienced many symptoms between ages 10-20. In my early 20's, my symptoms lessened and I had not had a flare in over 15 years.  The first day after vaccination, mild soreness in my left arm...no big deal, just a vaccine.  By the third day after my vaccination, I realized I was having pain in multiple joints, left wrist, hand and shoulder.  As the days passed, the pain and swelling in my joints continued and spread throughout my entire body.  I tried to wait in out in hopes the issues would resolve themselves.  Finally, after 6 weeks, I realized I was having a flare and made an appointment with my doctor who said she had other autoimmune patients experience the same thing but since it had been so long, she could prescribe steroids (which I had used during other lupus flares in my childhood) and that should resolve things.  I have since had 4 rounds of steroids of varying doses and am on hydroxychloroquine but, as soon as the steroid round ends, the pain and swelling increase again.  I cannot open bottles, have difficulty sleeping due to pain, cannot perform many of my duties at work and am overall able to do minimal physical activity.  My knuckles have turned into dimples and my fingers are 2 ring sizes larger than normal.  Prescriptions listed below.  This is the most expensive free vaccine I've ever received and also has had the most negative impact.  I sincerely hope we can stop the Lupus which remained dormant for the last 15 years before vaccination.  This has the potential to have major long term health impacts.  4/29/21: 20mg prednisone for 4 days, 10 mg for 3 days 5/10/21: 20mg prednisone for 4 days, 10 mg for 3 days 5/28/21: 40mg prednisone for 5 days 6/8/21: 5mg prednisone for 14 days
